Right to Lodge a Complaint
If you have concerns about our handling of your personal data, you have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
Legal Basis for Processing
We process your personal data on the basis of your consent, to fulfill our contractual obligations, for compliance with legal obligations, or for our legitimate interests where those interests are not overridden by your data protection rights.
GDPR, CCPA, LGPD, and VCDPA Rights
GDPR:
For users in the EU, you have rights under the General Data Protection Regulation, including access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data portability, and the right to object to processing.
CCPA:
California residents have rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act, including the right to know, delete, and opt-out of the sale of personal data.
LGPD:
For users in Brazil, rights under the Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados include confirmation of data processing, access, correction, anonymization, blocking, deletion, and data portability.
VCDPA:
Virginia residents have rights under the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act similar to those under GDPR and CCPA.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
I may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. I will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
This policy is effective as of 2025-01-28.